(59, 0, 8, 3, 'DragonBall Z: Battle 100 Multiplayer - Part 1 (DBZ Xenoverse Training)', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7ExO_koTv8E', 16.4, 1, 'Please LIKE the video ◕‿◕. Comment with your thoughts below, and Subscribe to make sure you don''t miss the next video! Thank You!\n\nDragonBall Z: Tenkaichi Tag Team Playlist: ✔ \nhttps://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL6HJK5FYYoPHETCthk4HqiajEL2Yyy7aM\n\n✘FatalBrotherHood:  https://www.youtube.com/user/FatalBrotherHood \n\nDragon Ball Z Tenkaichi Tag Team:(Link to buy it on Amazon, I am not sponsored or endorsed by them, I am simply trying to promote a game that I love):\nhttp://www.amazon.com/Dragon-Ball-Tenkaichi-Tag-Team-Sony/dp/B003LDKJEA/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&qid=1409716182&sr=8-1&keywords=dragon+ball+z+tenkaichi+tag+team\n\nDragonBall Z: Tenkaichi Tag Team Overview:\nDragon Ball Z: Tenkaichi Tag Team is the first Tenkaichi game to be featured on the PSP. A demo was released on PSN on October 19th. It featured Goku, Vegeta, Piccolo, Krillin, Android 19 and Dr. Gero as playable characters.Tenkaichi Tag Team is the first Tenkaichi game that does not include characters from Dragon Ball GT and Dragon Ball, but it is the first Dragon Ball Z game to feature the cast of Dragon Ball Z Kai.It is also the first Tenkaichi game to feature 1 vs 2, 2 vs 1 and 2 vs 2 battles, beside the general 1 vs 1.Goku and Gohan battle Trunks and Vegeta in a tag team battle. The gameplay is very similar to that of the Budokai Tenkaichi series. Players are able to play solo or team up via "Ad-Hoc" mode to tackle memorable battles in a variety of single player and multiplayer modes, including Dragon Walker, Battle 100, and Survival Mode. The game does team attacks. It features 70 playable and deeply customizable characters, multiple modes, and Ad-Hoc Party gameplay. The game has only English voice overs and excludes the Japanese voice overs. The English voice actors are those of Dragon Ball Z Kai instead of the FUNimation dub voice actors which have been there in all the previous Dragon Ball Z games.\n\nGame Modes\nDragon Walker\nThe Dragon Walker mode takes players through the entire Dragon Ball Z story arc from the Saiyan Saga to the Majin Buu Saga. This mode features classic stages similar to the what is happening in the storyline at that very point and the stage changes as the saga does. It enables you to move into the virtually liberal environment and hover over to the different places and do side missions or play minigames or directly jump into battle with your enemy by joining with them.\n\nDragonBall Z Xenoverse will be featuring multiple players in a single match similar to DragonBall Z Battle of Z. In order to prepare for "DragonBall Z Xenoverse" I decided to play "DragonBall Z Tenkaichi Tag Team" since the game features the perfect 2v2 combat system and the gameplay shown in "Xenoverse" has also displayed that it''ll be able to handle more than 1v1 combat situations. "Dragon Ball z Xenoverse" will be featuring a very similar character roster and is highly inspired by Dragon Ball Z MMO. "Dragon Ball Z Xenoverse Characters" will be highly customizable. "Dragon Ball Z Xenoverse Level Up!" will also be featuring a brand new unique storyline and might even be open world! "Dragon Ball Z Xenoverse Online" will be where all the legendary battle will be fought. For more "dragon ball xenoverse news" make sure you stay tuned to my channel!\n\nYou can talk to me directly here, most of the time:\n✘ Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/LegendarySuperSaiyanPaul\n✘ Twitter: https://twitter.com/SuperSaiyanPaul\n✘Twitch: http://www.twitch.tv/SuperSaiyanPaul\n\nCheckout my Bros for more videos!\n✘FatalBrotherHood: https://www.youtube.com/user/FatalBrotherHood ✘UnrealEntGaming: https://www.youtube.com/user/UnrealEntGaming', '2015-03-01 11:01:03', 'http://i3.ytimg.com/vi/7ExO_koTv8E/mqdefault.jpg', NULL, 1),
